casebody.data:
No. 268,

Misc.

Reed v. Beto, Corrections Director. Charles W. Tessmer, Clyde W. Woody and Emmett Colvin, Jr., for petitioner. Waggoner Carr, Attorney General of Texas, Hawthorne Phillips, First Assistant Attorney General, T. B. Wright, Executive Assistant Attorney General, and Gilbert J. Pena, Charles B. Swanner and Howard M. Fender, Assistant Attorneys General, for respondent.

C. A. 5th Cir. Motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and petition for writ of certiorari granted. The case is transferred to the appellate docket and set for oral argument immediately following No. 273, Mise.
